y 1894) Fabian Tract, 51\n*[[S Webb]], 'The reform of the House of Lords' (1917) Fabian Tract, 183\n\n;Books\n*[[W Bagehot]], ''[[The English Constitution]]'' (1867)\n*[[Lord Bingham of Cornhill]], ''Rule of Law'' (2010) \n*[[AV Dicey]], ''Introduction to the Study of the Law of the Constitution'' ([https://archive.org/stream/introductiontos04dicegoog#page/n6/mode/2up 3rd edn 1889]) \n*[[H Arendt]], ''[[Eichmann in Jerusalem: A Report on the Banality of Evil]]'' (1963)\n*[[J Froissart]], ''[[Froissart's Chronicles]]'' (1385) translated by GC Macaulay ([https://archive.org/stream/chroniclesfrois00macagoog#page/n12/mode/2up 1895])\n*[[I Jennings]], ''A Federation for Western Europe'' ([https://archive.org/stream/federationforwes031229mbp#page/n5/mode/2up/search/Kingdom 1940])\n*[[J Locke]], ''[[Two Treatises of Government]]'' ([https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Two_Treatises_of_Government 1689]) [https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Two_Treatises_of_Government/Book_II Book II, An Essay Concerning the True Origin, Extent, and End of Civil Government] \n*[[FW Maitland]], ''The Constitutional History of England'' ([https://archive.org/stream/constitutionalhi029314mbp#page/n5/mode/2up CUP 1919]) \n*[[JS Mill]], ''[[On Liberty]]'' ([https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/On_Liberty 1859])\n*[[JS Mill]], ''[[Considerations on Representative Government]]'' ([https://archive.org/stream/considerations00mill#page/n7/mode/2up 1861]) \n*[[T More]], ''[[Utopia (book)|Utopia]]'' (1516) translated by [[Gilbert Burnet]] ([https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Utopia_(1901) 1901])\n*[[FL Neumann]], ''Behemoth: The Structure and Practice of National Socialism, 1933-1944'' (1944) \n*[[FL Neumann]], ''The Democratic and the Authoritarian State: Essays in Political and Legal Theory'' (1957)\n*C Turpin and A Tomkins, ''British Government and the Constitution'' (7th edition, CUP)\n*[[S Webb]] and [[B Webb]], ''[[Industrial Democracy]]'' (1890)\n*[[S Webb]], ''English Local Government'' (1906 through 1929) Volumes 